ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: An overview of many biophysical techniques
Yes! Gives a good overview of spectroscopy

I would recommend the course to another student. It was a good survey of modern techniques, which would bring a graduate student up to date. It was also useful in learning how to analyze, critique, and present written research.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Like I have stated above, the course was very good at addressing the fundamental aspects of a graduate education. This includes critiquing the literature, asking good questions, proposing research, and understanding what can and can't be answered with certain methods or how experiments are conducted.
